<DOC><DOCNO> AP881023-0018 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-23-88 1130EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-India-Fire     10-23 0122</FIRST><SECOND>AM-India-Fire,0125</SECOND><HEAD>Four Die Of Burns From Factory Fire</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Four people injured in a fire at anillegal plastics factory died and at least 15 were hospitalized incritical condition Sunday, news reports said.   A gas cylinder exploded in the factory Saturday, setting off ablaze that destroyed the building and injured 45 people,authorities said.   The Press Trust of India news agency quoted a hospital officialas saying that many of the injured were expected to die of theirburns.   The plant in northwestern New Delhi was operating without alicense said a police official, speaking on condition of anonymity.   It took more than 100 firefighters about three hours to bringthe blaze under control.</TEXT></DOC>